Description.SourceString: After flying through a Bleed, perforated and burnt, this biplane was destined to become scrap.
As time passed, though, it seemed to be in better shape than originally thought.
With no work by the engineers, it was curiously back in flying shape.
But it no longer belonged to the war effort. It belonged to… something else.
Mikaela’s café was emblazoned with a logo that was undoubtedly Mikaela.
Black coffee is on the menu, but black magic is strictly forbidden.
Her running team came up with some less-than-flattering nicknames for her, but she imagined herself like a shark: it’s only a matter of time before she would catch anyone in her path.
A gifted storyteller, Mikaela was quick to offer a helping hand—be it a hot cup of joe or a mystical spell
She shattered regional records at her last high school meet. Those records remain unbroken to this day.
He experimented with cameras as a way to document his murders.
When his coworker called in sick, he reluctantly covered the shift. It would be his last.
A roll of film he never developed. Its contents have been exposed to the light and are lost forever.
There are for more efficient brooms on the market, but it’s not about that: it’s about the aesthetic.
These masks represent the wide range of human emotion: the joy of killing, and the sorrow of not having someone to kill anymore.
A vessel with the powerful ability to make dry turkey palatable.
A tiny toy automobile found on the dashboard of a compacted car from Autohaven.
With a full scholarship for track, Meg was excited to start a new chapter of her life at college.  This letter was as close as she got.
Even in death, that infernal cawing never stops.
Is it a trick of the light? Or is something really emerging?
Occasionally, the crows go on holiday to creepily stare at tourists.
Nothing appealed to him more than a good scary story.
He planned his murders tirelessly, architecting a death that would terrify the world.
An underground paper made a joke of him, and threatened to destroy his legacy.
All of his careful planning fell to pieces when he saw the paper's headquarters, and he entered a murderous rage.
Without his mask, or his method, he created a new story that night.
The first of a series of tarot cards that came to Mikaela in a dream. She felt paralyzed in her writing, unable to create or perform.
The second tarot card from her dream. Memories of forgetting her words, freezing on stage, choking flooded her mind.
The third card from her dream. She pondered what storytelling even meant to her. Was it created? Or remembered?
The fourth card from her dream. She shed the rules imposed on her by prescriptivist teachers and wrote with her heart.
The fifth card from her dream. Once she found her voice, the audience listened on bated breath, enraptured.
Where did they get the tiny body parts to build him?
This is the longest she has ever stood still.
Take a bite of it before it takes a bite of you.
When it’s one versus all, sometimes you have to make do with any weapon you can find.
A 3D representation of a terrifying son of a coal magnate.
A 3D representation of a hardened street racer.
A 3D representation of a chilling ghost.
A lovingly painted miniature Dwight… but painted by whom?
A delicious gummy layer surrounds what may or not be an actual spider.
Do they taste like cherry? Or do they just taste like blood? Only one way to find out. Design inspired by Maomi.
Maurice is missing, but in his place, a milk carton with a picture of Maurice mysteriously appeared. Design inspired by PotatoGun13.
A bright light who will always have a place fighting alongside friends in The Fog.
It’s difficult to find something that provides protection in The Entity’s Realm, but it’s worth a shot.
